PART 1: THE PROJECTIVE PLANE HIERARCHY PG(2, F_q)
======================================================================

  PG(2, F_q) has q^2 + q + 1 points, q^2 + q + 1 lines
  Each line has q + 1 points, each point on q + 1 lines
  It's a Steiner system S(2, q+1, q^2+q+1)

    q= 2: |PG(2,F_q)| =    7 points, 3 per line = H_forb_1 !!!
           Steiner S(2, 3, 7)

    q= 3: |PG(2,F_q)| =   13 points, 4 per line = F(7) = Fibonacci prime
           Steiner S(2, 4, 13)

    q= 4: |PG(2,F_q)| =   21 points, 5 per line = H_forb_2 !!!
           Steiner S(2, 5, 21)

    q= 5: |PG(2,F_q)| =   31 points, 6 per line = 2^5 - 1 (Mersenne)
           Steiner S(2, 6, 31)

    q= 7: |PG(2,F_q)| =   57 points, 8 per line = 3*19
           Steiner S(2, 8, 57)

    q= 8: |PG(2,F_q)| =   73 points, 9 per line = ACHIEVABLE H (not forbidden)
           Steiner S(2, 9, 73)

    q= 9: |PG(2,F_q)| =   91 points, 10 per line = 7*13
           Steiner S(2, 10, 91)

    q=11: |PG(2,F_q)| =  133 points, 12 per line = 7*19
           Steiner S(2, 12, 133)

